From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Fri, 12 Jun 2026 10:54:08 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): add `runs doctor` journal health checker with
 mechanical repair
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add `flowai-workflow runs doctor --workflow <dir> --run <id>` (FR-E83): a
read-only diagnosis of a run's durability artifacts plus a bounded `--repair`
that touches only the two safe mechanical faults.

- Journal integrity: missing file / mid-file garbage / unknown kind are ERRORs;
  torn final line, non-monotonic seq, duplicate event_id are WARNINGs.
- Replay invariants via the EXISTING replayer (no second replayer): events
  after a terminal run event, lifecycle events for undeclared nodes,
  attempt_completed without attempt_started, and replayed total_cost_usd
  diverging from the per-node cost facts are ERRORs.
- Filesystem cross-check: orphan node dirs, journal-declared dirs missing on
  disk, and a stale runs/.lock for this run are WARNINGs (advisory — the engine
  declares node dirs eagerly but creates them lazily).
- `--repair`: torn-line removal (backup .bak + atomic tmp+rename) and stale-lock
  removal; refuses, modifying nothing, on a live lock or any non-torn error.
- `--json` emits a stable findings list (severity, code, message, evidence);
  exit 0 when no ERRORs, 1 otherwise.

Reuses getRunDir/getJournalPath/defaultLockPath; adds classifyRunLock to
lock.ts (centralizes lock-file knowledge) and RUN_JOURNAL_EVENT_KINDS to
run-journal.ts. Registers FR-E83 in the engine SRS + index.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
