+### 3.83 FR-E83: Runs Doctor — Journal Health Check and Mechanical Repair
+
+- **Description:** `flowai-workflow runs doctor --workflow <dir> --run <id>`
+  diagnoses a run's durability artifacts and, with `--repair`, applies only
+  safe mechanical fixes. A run's sole durable record is its append-only
+  `journal.jsonl` (replayed by `replayRunJournal`); crashes, manual tampering,
+  and engine bugs can degrade it or the surrounding run directory. Doctor
+  reports EVERY problem found grouped by severity (ERROR / WARNING / OK), exits
+  0 when no ERRORs and 1 otherwise, and never writes a second replayer — it
+  orchestrates the existing replayer and inspects the result.
+
+  **Checks (in order):**
+  1. **Journal integrity** — file exists; every line parses; a truncated/garbage
+     FINAL line is a WARNING (the writer already tolerates it); a non-final
+     unparseable line and an unknown event `kind` are ERRORs; non-monotonic
+     `seq` and duplicate `event_id` are WARNINGs (the replayer dedupes).
+  2. **Replay invariants** — via the EXISTING replayer: events after a terminal
+     run event, node-lifecycle events for undeclared nodes, `attempt_completed`
+     without a matching `attempt_started`, and replayed `total_cost_usd`
+     diverging from the per-node `cost_usd` facts are each ERRORs.
+  3. **Filesystem cross-check** — orphan node dirs, journal-declared dirs absent
+     on disk, and a `runs/.lock` for this run held by a dead process (stale
+     lock) are WARNINGs.
+
+  **`--repair`** applies only: torn-final-line removal (backup `journal.jsonl.bak`
+  then atomic tmp+rename) and stale-lock removal. It REFUSES, modifying nothing,
+  when the run is active (live lock) or the journal has any error beyond the
+  torn final line. **`--json`** emits a machine-readable findings list
+  (severity, code, message, evidence path).
+- **Motivation:** Recovery depends on a healthy journal; operators need a
+  read-only diagnosis and a bounded, non-guessing repair for the one mechanical
+  corruption the writer already anticipates (the torn crash tail) without
+  hand-editing durable state.
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - **Tests:** `doctor_test.ts` (FR-E83; regression-locked; clean run exit 0,
+    torn tail, mid-file garbage, unknown kind, event-after-terminal, cost-sum
+    divergence, orphan dir, missing declared dir, stale lock, `--repair`
+    torn-line round-trip, repair refusals on live lock and garbage, `--json`
+    shape) and `cli_test.ts` (FR-E83; `runs doctor` in `--help`, arg parsing).
+
