+## Solution
+
+### Files
+
+- NEW `src/state/doctor.ts` — diagnosis + repair + rendering core.
+- NEW `src/state/doctor_test.ts` — unit tests on fabricated run dirs.
+- EDIT `src/state/lock.ts` — export `classifyRunLock(workflowDir, runId)` →
+  `{ status: "absent"|"live"|"stale"|"other-run"|"corrupt", info?, path }`,
+  reusing `readLockInfo` + (now-shared) `isProcessAlive`.
+- EDIT `src/state/run-journal.ts` — export
+  `RUN_JOURNAL_EVENT_KINDS: readonly RunJournalEventKind[]` (single source for
+  the doctor's unknown-kind check).
+- EDIT `src/cli.ts` — `runs doctor` dispatch, `parseDoctorArgs`, `runDoctor`,
+  help text line.
+- EDIT `src/cli_test.ts` — help + parseDoctorArgs tests.
+- EDIT SRS (FR-E83) + `documents/index.md`.
+
+### doctor.ts API
+
+- `type DoctorSeverity = "error" | "warning"`.
+- `interface DoctorFinding { severity; code; message; evidence }`.
+- `interface DoctorReport { runId; findings: DoctorFinding[]; okGroups: string[] }`.
+- `interface RepairAction { code; message }`.
+- `interface RepairOutcome { refused: boolean; reason?: string; actions: RepairAction[] }`.
+- `hasErrors(report): boolean`.
+- `diagnoseRun({ workflowDir, runId }): Promise<DoctorReport>`.
+- `repairRun({ workflowDir, runId }): Promise<{ report; outcome }>` — diagnoses,
+  then applies/refuses.
+- `renderReport(report, outcome?): string` — human-readable, grouped by
+  severity + OK summary.
+- `toJson(report, outcome?): object` — machine-readable.
+
+### Diagnosis algorithm
+
+1. `runDir = getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)`; `journalPath = getJournalPath(runDir)`.
+2. Read journal. NotFound → ERROR `journal_missing`; still run lock check; return.
+3. Integrity scan (line-by-line, mirrors replayer's torn-tail rule:
+   `endedWithNewline = content.endsWith("\n")`, split, pop trailing empty):
+   parse each non-empty line; on parse failure → torn tail (last line &&
+   !endedWithNewline) `journal_torn_tail` WARNING + record valid byte length,
+   else `journal_garbage_line` ERROR. On success: kind ∉
+   `RUN_JOURNAL_EVENT_KINDS` → `journal_unknown_kind` ERROR; track prev seq for
+   `journal_seq_non_monotonic` WARNING; track event_id set for
+   `journal_duplicate_event_id` WARNING.
+4. Replay invariants: `try { replay = await replayRunJournal(runDir) }`. On
+   throw → if no integrity ERROR already recorded, add `replay_failed` ERROR;
+   skip field checks. On success, over `replay.events` (file order):
+   - first terminal index (`run_completed/failed/aborted`); each later event →
+     `event_after_terminal` ERROR.
+   - declared = node_ids from `node_declared`; each
+     node_started/completed/failed/waiting/skipped with node_id ∉ declared →
+     `node_never_declared` ERROR.
+   - track `attempt_started` keys (`node_id#iteration`); each `attempt_completed`
+     with no prior matching key → `attempt_completed_unmatched` ERROR.
+   - `recordedSum` = Σ top-level `cost_usd` over the last
+     node_completed/node_failed per node (from the integrity-parsed events);
+     if `|recordedSum - (replay.state.total_cost_usd ?? 0)| > 1e-9` →
+     `cost_sum_divergence` ERROR.
+5. Filesystem cross-check (uses parsed `node_directory_declared` events even if
+   replay failed): for each declared node_dir, derive its path suffix after
+   `runs/<runId>/`; stat → missing → `declared_dir_missing` WARNING. Walk the
+   run dir (top level + one level into declared phase containers), skip reserved
+   `logs`/`.hitl-inbox`; a directory matching no declared node dir →
+   `orphan_node_dir` WARNING.
+6. Lock check: `classifyRunLock(workflowDir, runId)`; `"stale"` →
+   `stale_lock` WARNING.
+
+### Repair algorithm (`repairRun`)
+
+1. `diagnoseRun`. 2. Refuse (nothing modified) if lock status `"live"`
+   (`reason: run active`) OR any ERROR finding whose code ≠ the torn-tail
+   warning (i.e. any ERROR at all) (`reason: journal has errors beyond torn
+   final line`). 3. Else apply: if `journal_torn_tail` present →
+   `copyFile(journal, journal.bak)`, write valid-prefix to `journal.jsonl.tmp`,
+   `rename` over journal; action `repaired_torn_line`. If `stale_lock` present
+   → `Deno.remove(lockPath)`; action `removed_stale_lock`.
+
+### Error handling
+
+- All FS reads guard `Deno.errors.NotFound`. Replay throw is caught and mapped
+  to a finding, never propagated. Lock parse errors → `classifyRunLock` returns
+  `"corrupt"` (no throw). Repair is refusal-gated; partial writes avoided via
+  backup-then-atomic-rename.
+
+### CLI wiring
+
+- `Deno.args[0] === "runs"` && `Deno.args[1] === "doctor"` → `runDoctor(args.slice(2))`.
+- `parseDoctorArgs`: `--workflow <dir>`/`=`, `--run <id>`/`=`, `--repair`, `--json`;
+  throw on missing `--workflow`/`--run`.
+- `runDoctor`: diagnose or repair; print `renderReport` or `JSON.stringify(toJson)`;
+  exit 0 if (no --repair && !hasErrors) || (--repair && !refused); else 1.
+- Add `runs doctor` to `printUsage`.
+
+### Verification
+
+- `deno test -A src/state/doctor_test.ts src/cli_test.ts`
+- `deno task check`
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- (defer) MCP `runs doctor` tool + batch multi-run mode — out of scope here.
